description: Arcade warriors battle it out for supremacy of the digital domain, but the true field may be one more of digital manipulation and analog input than knock-outs and super moves! Cosplayers will chase down the writer of their favorite erotica to submit themselves as slaves to their whims, while big sis will make sure her younger brother knows his place in the world. As the world turns, a salaryman may find solace in the arms of a titillating teenager, while two moms may find the solution to their lonely problems in their teenager’s friends (or even boyfriend)! Much like this collection of short stories by Maban, the world is filled with Passionate Lovers!
name: Vol. 1

description: Committed to comprehending his Inhuman ability to see the future, Ulysses begins training within Karnak's Tower—but has he made the right choice? Struck with a grisly vision, Ulysses must again come to terms with the magnitude of his power... and the limitations!
name: Tower of Wisdom, Part III

volume.name: Civil War II: Ulysses Infinite Comic

description:
Siblings Ian and John Jenkins were both R.A.F. pilots. Ian was the elder, calm and confident. John was younger and hot-headed, a definite firebrand. Based in the North-East of Scotland, they protected the coast against attack from the marauding Luftwaffe.

However, when tragedy struck, John found himself embroiled in a mystery — one that involved death, destruction and even espionage. And it seemed there was a family connection. The firebrand was determined to find the answers…whatever the cost.
name: Firebrand!

description:
“Flame Squadron” they were called in the R.A.F. But to the baffled pilots of the Luftwaffe they were known as “Flame Devils”.

When an aircraft was shot to pieces, cartwheeling across the sky in a mass of flames, somewhere in that blazing Spitfire a cool fighting brain still functioned, a finger still pressed the firing button. Long after any pilot must have perished, each plane carried on flying.

As the Luftwaffe’s terror grew, one of Germany’s top spies was sent to ferret out the secret of the “Flame Devils”…
name: Fighter Ace

description:
When World War II broke out Mark Enfield quit his office job and enlisted in the army. Although enthusiastic, he was quite puny and unfit. Nor was he a very good shot — and many noted the irony that he shared his surname with the famous Lee Enfield rifle that they used.

He became a target of bullies among his fellow recruits in basic training and this continued when they went into battle.

However, Mark was determined to stand up to his detractors once and for all, especially when his unit was tasked with destroying a strategically important bridge which was in enemy hands.
name: Making His Mark

description:
During the war most people served in the same unit all the time. However, Jack Banham was different. He was in an Italian jail, then a front-line trench with the Greek army, then the observer’s cockpit of an Italian biplane. At one time he was even a colonel in the Greek army…

…Or was it the Greek air force? Months afterwards he still wasn’t sure. Not that it mattered, for by that time he was a pilot in the Fleet Air Arm!
name: Burning Skies

description: The conclusion to the Battle of Berlin! You don’t want to miss out on this explosive finale!
name: Chapter 54

description: It's the end of the road for Lance. He's made it this far but still has one task left. It'll take a herculean effort to get through this one – it's the last issue of the FREELANCE BLUES mini-series!
name: Chapter 6: Family Business

description: Each issue of Marvel Previews is a comic book-sized, 120-page, full-color guide and preview to all of Marvel's upcoming releases - it's your #1 source for advanced information on Marvel Comics! This August issue features items scheduled to ship in October 2016 and beyond.

The internationally wanted vigilante Soldier: 76 heads to Egypt to track down a lead, which takes him to an unexpected reunion.

Note: Comixology released this issue a day before Dark Horse.
name: Ana: Old Soldiers

description:
Dream

Having lost nearly everything, the survivors of the fallen city wander the woods in search of a new home. Luke lies in a coma, Donna struggles with an unknown power, and Jane and Becky are prisoners of the Veratu, where being returned to the Gloom has become a much more deadly process than before. Learn the origin of the Cleaners, see how the rest of the world has fared under the Gloom, and discover a dark secret of the Veratu as the final act of the saga begins!
name: Dream

description:
Antarctic Press raids shelves with a spectacular new crimefighting adolescent courtesy of writer John Crowther and legendary artist Dell Barras!

It's tough being different, especially when you're a teenager, but Rochelle Planeta is a survivor like none other -- a human cockroach! Get ready for a Mind Crash as Rochelle journeys into cyberspace to battle Terrorbyte and stop him from drawing addicted players into his domain!

Note: The digital edition (7/27/2016) for this issue was released before the print edition.

What is the price of peace? Assassins circle as Anduin reads a letter from his father, King Varian, and ponders the responsibilities of leadership. The young prince must face his fears and decide if he can defend Azeroth and keep true to his beliefs.
name: Anduin: Son of the Wolf
